## 1. Introduction
This project aims to develop a web-based **Student Management System (SMS)** integrated with **Artificial Intelligence** to automate and improve student data handling. Inspired by systems like Fedena and Campus 365, it allows students to check their marks, syllabus, fees, and more in a secure and user-friendly interface.

## 2. Objectives
- Centralize student data management.
- Enable AI-driven performance insights.
- Improve academic transparency for students and faculty.

## 3. Functional Requirements
- Student login and access to personal data, marks, syllabus, fees, and faculty info.
- Admin can add/edit/delete student records.
- Faculty can upload marks, syllabus, and assign subjects.
- AI module gives suggestions or flags for academic risk.

## 4. Non-Functional Requirements
- Role-based access control.
- Secure password encryption.
- Responsive web interface.

## 5. System Features
- Dashboard for each user role.
- AI predictions on student performance.
- Notification system for updates (optional).

## 6. Tools & Technologies
- Backend: Python (Flask or Django)
- Frontend: HTML/CSS, Bootstrap, JavaScript
- Database: MySQL
- AI: Scikit-learn or TensorFlow (for performance predictions)

## 7. Use Case Overview
**Actors:** Student, Faculty, Admin  
**Use Cases:** Login, View Data, Upload Marks, Manage Records, AI Analysis

## 8. Future Scope
- Integration with SMS/email alerts
- Real-time analytics dashboards
- Biometric or OTP-based secure logins

